nodes.title: ElevenLabs
nodes.desc: A platform providing AI-powered voice cloning and audio editing tools for content creators. [More Info](https://elevenlabs.io/)

nodes.title: Artificial Intelligence
nodes.desc: The development of computer systems able to perform tasks that typically require human intelligence, such as speech recognition and decision-making. [More Info](https://www.ibm.com/watson/what-is-artificial-intelligence)

nodes.title: Audio Signal Processing
nodes.desc: The manipulation and analysis of audio signals to extract information or improve quality. [More Info](https://www.aes.org/publications/standards/AES24-2-2014.pdf)

nodes.title: Digital Signal Processing
nodes.desc: The study of signals in a digital representation and the processing methods of these signals. [More Info](https://www.dspguide.com/)

nodes.title: ElevenLabs API
nodes.desc: A set of APIs provided by ElevenLabs for developers to integrate voice cloning and audio editing capabilities into their applications. [More Info](https://docs.elevenlabs.io/)

nodes.title: ElevenLabs Studio
nodes.desc: A web-based platform for creating and editing audio content using ElevenLabs' voice cloning and audio editing tools. [More Info](https://studio.elevenlabs.io/)

nodes.title: ElevenLabs Community
nodes.desc: A community of users and developers sharing knowledge, resources, and projects related to ElevenLabs' technology. [More Info](https://community.elevenlabs.io/)

nodes.title: Voice Cloning
nodes.desc: The process of creating a digital replica of a person's voice, often used in voice assistants, audiobooks, and video production. [More Info](https://www.voicebot.ai/voice-cloning/)

nodes.title: Audio Editing
nodes.desc: The process of manipulating and editing audio files to achieve a desired sound or effect. [More Info](https://www.adobe.com/audition.html)

nodes.title: Content Creation
nodes.desc: The process of creating and publishing content, such as videos, podcasts, and blog posts, for various mediums. [More Info](https://www.contentmarketinginstitute.com/)

nodes.title: Machine Learning
nodes.desc: A subset of artificial intelligence that involves training algorithms to learn from data and make predictions or decisions. [More Info](https://www.tensorflow.org/)

nodes.title: Deep Learning
nodes.desc: A type of machine learning that uses neural networks with multiple layers to analyze data. [More Info](https://www.deeplearning.ai/)

nodes.title: Neural Networks
nodes.desc: A series of algorithms that seek to recognize underlying relationships in a set of data through a process that mimics the way the human brain operates. [More Info](https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/B9780128113185000027)

nodes.title: Speech Recognition
nodes.desc: The ability of a computer to identify and transcribe spoken language. [More Info](https://www.speechmatics.com/)

nodes.title: Natural Language Processing
nodes.desc: A subfield of artificial intelligence that deals with the interaction between computers and humans in natural language. [More Info](https://www.nltk.org/)
